been used to treat gallstones. A few of the most commonly prescribed are Berberis vulgaris, Lycopodium clavatum, Podophyllum peltatum, and Sarsaparilla Officinalis. To ensure that you are taking the correct remedy for your condition, discuss your treatment plan with a professional.</p><li style="list-style-type: disc"><h4 class="">What are the best homeopathic drops for gallstones?</h4><p class="saswp-faq-answer-text">Homeopathic drops such as Berberis Vulgaris, Berberis Aquifolium, and Carduus Marianus can help treat gallstones. These drops work to break down gallstones and reduce inflammation in the gallbladder. Additionally, these homeopathic drops cleanse the liver and improve overall digestion health.</p></ul></div>
